  <summary date="2025-09-09T18:52:28Z" status="Introduced in House">More Homes on the Market Act 

This bill increases the amount of gain from the sale of a principal residence that an individual may exclude from gross income (for federal tax purposes).

Under the bill, an individual may exclude from gross income gain from the sale of a principal residence of up to $500,000 (currently $250,000), and taxpayers who are married and file a joint federal income tax return may exclude up to $1 million (currently $500.000).&#160;The bill also requires these amounts to be adjusted annually for inflation.</summary>
</bill>
